---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — 404found.studio"
  description="Privacy Policy for 404found.studio. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data in compliance with Malaysia's PDPA 2010."
  canonicalURL="https://404found.studio/privacy"
  noindex={false}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="legal-main">

    <div class="legal-header">
      <p class="legal-label">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-meta">Effective date: 1 January 2025 · Last updated: 30 June 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">

      <p class="legal-intro">
        404Found Studio ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard information when you visit <strong>404found.studio</strong> or engage our services. We comply with Malaysia's <strong>Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA 2010)</strong>.
      </p>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p>404Found Studio is a web development and digital technology company based in Malaysia. We build websites, web applications, SaaS platforms, and digital systems for businesses. We also operate our own digital products and platforms.</p>
        <p>For data protection purposes, 404Found Studio is the data controller for personal data collected through this website and our direct client engagements.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following categories of personal data:</p>

        <h3>Information you provide directly</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Name, email address, phone number submitted via contact forms or WhatsApp</li>
          <li>Business name and website URL when requesting a quote</li>
          <li>Conversation content submitted through our AI Consultant chat tool</li>
          <li>Project briefs, files, or documents you share with us during an engagement</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>IP address, browser type, device type, and operating system</li>
          <li>Pages visited, time spent, and navigation patterns on this website</li>
          <li>Referral source (how you arrived at our website)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information from third-party tools</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — aggregated website traffic and behaviour data</li>
          <li><strong>Microsoft Clarity</strong> — session recordings and heatmaps for UX improvement (anonymised)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>We do not collect sensitive personal data (such as financial account details, health information, or national identity numbers) through this website.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>We use the personal data we collect for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>To respond to enquiries</strong> — contacting you about your project request or consultation</li>
          <li><strong>To provide our services</strong> — managing your project, communicating updates, and delivering agreed deliverables</li>
          <li><strong>To process payments</strong> — issuing invoices and processing fees via our payment gateway partners</li>
          <li><strong>To improve our website</strong> — analysing usage data to enhance user experience and content</li>
          <li><strong>To send relevant communications</strong> — project updates, invoices, or (with your consent) occasional service updates</li>
          <li><strong>To comply with legal obligations</strong> — retaining business and financial records as required by Malaysian law</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not use your personal data for automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal or significant effects on you.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
        <p>Under PDPA 2010, we process your personal data on the following grounds:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consent</strong> — when you submit a contact form, start a chat, or provide your details voluntarily</li>
          <li><strong>Contractual necessity</strong> — when we need your data to fulfil a service agreement with you</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — for website analytics, portfolio display, and business improvement activities</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — for invoicing, tax records, and other regulatory compliance</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies on this website. These include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — required for basic website functionality (e.g. theme preference)</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — Google Analytics and Microsoft Clarity to understand how visitors use our site</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling analytics cookies will not affect your ability to use this website, but may limit our ability to improve it.</p>
        <p>Google Analytics data is processed under Google's Privacy Policy. Microsoft Clarity is processed under Microsoft's Privacy Statement. We have configured both tools to anonymise IP addresses where possible.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data to third parties. We may share your data with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Payment gateway providers</strong> — to process project fees (e.g. ToyyibPay, Stripe, Billplz). These providers have their own privacy policies and handle payment data independently.</li>
          <li><strong>Cloud and hosting providers</strong> — Cloudflare (website hosting and delivery), Supabase, and other infrastructure providers who process data on our behalf under data processing agreements.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication tools</strong> — WhatsApp, email providers, for correspondence purposes.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal authorities</strong> — if required by Malaysian law, court order, or government authority.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Where we share data with third-party processors, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes described in this policy:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Enquiry and contact data</strong> — 12 months from last contact, unless a project commences</li>
          <li><strong>Client project data</strong> — 5 years after project completion (for business record-keeping and warranty purposes)</li>
          <li><strong>Financial and invoice records</strong> — 7 years, as required under Malaysian tax and accounting law</li>
          <li><strong>Website analytics data</strong> — 14 months (Google Analytics default retention)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>After the retention period, data is securely deleted or anonymised.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Data from Our SaaS Platforms</h2>
        <p>We develop and operate SaaS platforms including but not limited to <strong>unlockedu.my</strong>, <strong>ezkhairat.com</strong>, <strong>kariah.my</strong>, and <strong>lokaljob.my</strong>. Each of these platforms has its own privacy policy governing data collected from users of those specific platforms.</p>
        <p>Data processed through those platforms is governed by the relevant platform's privacy policy and the terms agreed with the respective platform operator (our client), who acts as the data controller. 404Found Studio acts as a data processor in relation to those platforms.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Your Rights Under PDPA 2010</h2>
        <p>As a data subject under Malaysia's Personal Data Protection Act 2010, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li><strong>Correction</strong> — request that inaccurate or incomplete data be corrected</li>
          <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong> — withdraw consent for us to process your data (where consent is the legal basis), subject to contractual obligations</li>
          <li><strong>Limit processing</strong> — request that we restrict how we use your data in certain circumstances</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details in Section 11. We will respond within <strong>21 days</strong> of receiving your request. We may need to verify your identity before processing your request.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorised access, accidental loss, or destruction. These include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmitted through this website</li>
          <li>Access controls limiting who within our team can access client data</li>
          <li>Use of reputable, security-certified infrastructure providers</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Despite our efforts, no internet transmission is 100% secure. If you believe your data has been compromised, please contact us immediately.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>11. Contact & Complaints</h2>
        <p>For any privacy-related queries, data access requests, or complaints, please contact our data officer:</p>
        <div class="legal-contact">
          <p><strong>404Found Studio — Data Officer</strong></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@404found.studio">hello@404found.studio</a></p>
          <p>WhatsApp: <a href="https://wa.me/601155525587" target="_blank" rel="noopener">+60 11-5552 5587</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://404found.studio">404found.studio</a></p>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:1rem;">If you are unsatisfied with our response, you may lodge a complaint with the <strong>Department of Personal Data Protection Malaysia (JPDP)</strong> at <a href="https://www.pdp.gov.my" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pdp.gov.my</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. The updated policy will be published on this page with a revised effective date. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="legal-nav">
      <a href="/terms">→ Terms and Conditions</a>
      <a href="/refund">→ Refund Policy</a>
      <a href="/about">→ About Us</a>
    </div>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-main {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .legal-header {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .legal-label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text3);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .legal-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text2);
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
  }

  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text2);
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.85rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text2);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .legal-contact {
    background: var(--bg2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-contact p { margin-bottom: 0.35rem !important; }

  .legal-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-nav a {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .legal-nav a:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-main { padding: 4rem 1.5rem 5rem; }
    .legal-header { padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .legal-header h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
